          "question": "<p><a name=\"60246\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>Which of the following statements are true ?</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:upper-roman\">\n\t<li>A circuit that adds two bits, producing a sum bit and carry bit is called half adder.</li>\n\t<li>A circuit that adds two bits, producing a sum bit and carry bit is called full adder.</li>\n\t<li>A circuit that adds two bits and a carry bit producing a sum bit and a carry bit is called full adder.</li>\n\t<li>A device that accepts the value of a Boolean variable as input and produces its complement is called an inverter.\n\t\n\t</li>\n</ol></div><br><br><b>UGC NET CSE | December 2013 | Part 2 | Question: 40</b></p>",
